        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 3 at 5:33PM EDT until July 3 at 6:15PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>SVROKX

The National Weather Service in Upton NY has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Central Fairfield County in southern Connecticut...
Southwestern New Haven County in southern Connecticut...

* Until 615 PM EDT.

* At 533 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Weston, or 10
miles northwest of Bridgeport, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vehicles is possible. Expect wind
damage to trees and power lines.

* This severe thunderstorm will be near...
Bridgeport and Shelton around 540 PM EDT.
Stratford and Derby around 550 PM EDT.
Milford and Seymour around 555 PM EDT.
New Haven and Woodbridge around 600 PM EDT.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
